==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Turkish [[müezzin]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[موذن|مؤذن]]}}, lit. "one who calls (to prayer)".

===Alternative spellings===
*[[mouezzin]]

===Noun===
'''muezzin'''

# the servant in a [[mosque]] who calls to prayer from one of the [[minaret]]s.

